      "content": "I'm looking at some digitized census records from Lunenburg County, Virginia, around the 1780s. There's a really weird dip in the recorded population between the 1775 and 1790 counts that doesn't seem to align with the typical mortality rates from the Revolutionary War or known migration patterns to the frontier. Do you have any insight into what might cause those kinds of statistical fluctuations in that specific region and timeframe?",
